        <abstract> 
<p>Pleased that JM will allow two-thirds profits [on <hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi>] for he wants Krause to receive some profit.</p>  
<p>He and his son [Francis] are preparing a large botanical work [<hi rend="italic">Movement in plants</hi>], dry as dust, which he must publish on commission. He will be lucky to lose only £100.</p> 
        </abstract>
